Verifies that unsupported association resource types are skipped (e.g., Microsoft.Web/sites). If it is a successful verification the logs should show no handler was found and notificationProviderResult should be "false". Also, the test asserts no DCR payload contains that resource type

Associations are only checked for resource types listed in appsettings - we still listen and process notifications for other types (e.g., LAW) via WorkspaceNotificationsHandler. Also, going with the assumption that differences across clouds can only happen because of different list of association related RTs and non-association types in notifications are expected
fail right away and not go to the assoc provider
